{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2d1f6867-2e08-4e66-83ac-4f31eb6a4ae3","content":"You can add the `--hotreload` flag as a default command-line argument in your project file so it's always passed to the testing platform:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_q6OfVqUziZkCv2ZWKLDeQT","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c7cd1f66016748b58aa01f3779681c20/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--hotreload</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c7cd1f66016748b58aa01f3779681c20/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"d53d0c7d-5947-427b-b1ce-d1035b3b5dca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to enable hot reload for their test project so they don't need to set `DOTNET_WATCH_RESTART_ON_RUDE_EDIT` or similar environment variables every time. For .NET test projects, the way to get \"hot reload\" / watch mode is via `dotnet watch test`. \n\nBut actually, looking at this more carefully - in .NET 9 with the new testing platform (`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`), hot reload for tests can be enabled using `dotnet test --hotreload` or by configuring it in the project file or a runsettings file.\n\nWait, let me think about this differently. \n\nFor the Microsoft.Testing.Platform that this project uses, I can configure hot reload to always be enabled by adding a property to the `.csproj` file that sets the command line arguments. Setting the MSBuild property in the `.csproj` file seems like the cleanest solution for making hot reload the default behavior without needing to specify it manually each time.","outputTokens":943,"requestId":"EC56:75BF8:34ED94E:3A5C7DC:6A02FA51"},"id":"3fbcbcd5-eaf4-49fe-a761-a22c543182b4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:01:08.472Z","parentId":"a2f36087-c7b0-461d-8a66-aad88b804080"}
